---
// MultiAgentMetrics.astro — When multi-agent beats single agent
---

<div class="mam-wrap">
  <h3 class="mam-title">When Multi-Agent Is Worth the Complexity</h3>
  <p class="mam-sub">More agents = more cost. Here's when the trade-off pays off.</p>
  <div class="mam-grid">
    <div class="mam-card"><div class="mam-metric"><span class="mam-val mam-v--green">3.2x</span><span class="mam-delta">better</span></div><div class="mam-name">Complex Task Accuracy</div><div class="mam-desc">Multi-step research + writing tasks</div><div class="mam-bar-track"><div class="mam-bar mam-b--green" style="--w:92%"></div></div></div>
    <div class="mam-card"><div class="mam-metric"><span class="mam-val mam-v--cyan">2.1x</span><span class="mam-delta">faster</span></div><div class="mam-name">Parallel Execution</div><div class="mam-desc">When agents work simultaneously</div><div class="mam-bar-track"><div class="mam-bar mam-b--cyan" style="--w:78%"></div></div></div>
    <div class="mam-card"><div class="mam-metric"><span class="mam-val mam-v--amber">2.8x</span><span class="mam-delta">more $</span></div><div class="mam-name">Token Cost</div><div class="mam-desc">More agents = more LLM calls</div><div class="mam-bar-track"><div class="mam-bar mam-b--amber" style="--w:85%"></div></div></div>
    <div class="mam-card"><div class="mam-metric"><span class="mam-val mam-v--purple">67%</span><span class="mam-delta">fewer</span></div><div class="mam-name">Hallucinations</div><div class="mam-desc">Review agent catches made-up facts</div><div class="mam-bar-track"><div class="mam-bar mam-b--purple" style="--w:67%"></div></div></div>
  </div>
  <div class="mam-insight"><strong>Rule of thumb:</strong> If the task takes a single agent more than 5 reasoning steps, split it into specialized agents. Below 5 steps, a single agent is simpler and cheaper.</div>
</div>

<style>
  .mam-wrap { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0f172a, #1e293b); border-radius: 16px; padding: 2rem; margin: 2rem 0; border: 1px solid #334155; }
  .mam-title { color: #f1f5f9; font-size: 1.15rem; font-weight: 700; margin: 0 0 .25rem; }
  .mam-sub { color: #64748b; font-size: .8rem; margin: 0 0 1.5rem; font-family: monospace; }
  .mam-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit,minmax(200px,1fr)); gap: 12px; }
  .mam-card { background: rgba(0,0,0,.25); border: 1px solid #334155; border-radius: 12px; padding: 16px; }
  .mam-metric { display: flex; align-items: baseline; gap: 6px; margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .mam-val { font-size: 1.4rem; font-weight: 800; font-family: monospace; }
  .mam-v--green { color: #4ade80; } .mam-v--cyan { color: #06b6d4; } .mam-v--amber { color: #f59e0b; } .mam-v--purple { color: #818cf8; }
  .mam-delta { color: #64748b; font-size: .6rem; font-family: monospace; }
  .mam-name { color: #e2e8f0; font-size: .8rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 2px; }
  .mam-desc { color: #64748b; font-size: .65rem; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .mam-bar-track { height: 4px; background: rgba(0,0,0,.3); border-radius: 2px; overflow: hidden; }
  .mam-bar { height: 100%; border-radius: 2px; width: 0; animation: mamG 1.2s ease-out .5s forwards; }
  .mam-b--green { background: #4ade80; } .mam-b--cyan { background: #06b6d4; } .mam-b--amber { background: #f59e0b; } .mam-b--purple { background: #818cf8; }
  .mam-insight { margin-top: 14px; padding: 12px; border-radius: 10px; background: rgba(129,140,248,.05); border: 1px solid #818cf820; color: #94a3b8; font-size: .75rem; line-height: 1.6; }
  .mam-insight strong { color: #a5b4fc; }
  @keyframes mamG { to { width: var(--w); } }
</style>
